From a97b96569fbc5088b66bddf790580e447e7a3e82 Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: Matthew Feickert <matthew.feickert@cern.ch>
Date: Sat, 2 May 2026 12:30:08 -0600
Subject: [PATCH] configure: link libLHAPDF when LHAPDF support is enabled

In modern LHAPDF (>= 6.5.6), 'lhapdf-config --ldflags' returns only the
library search path ('-L<libdir>') while '--libs' returns both the
search path and the library flag ('-L<libdir> -lLHAPDF'). Older LHAPDF
releases included '-lLHAPDF' in '--ldflags', which is what Sherpa's
configure relied on.

Without '-lLHAPDF', libSherpaTools.so does not record libLHAPDF.so as a
NEEDED dependency, so the runtime loader does not pull it in, and the
first call to LHAPDF::Config::get() (via the inline LHAPDF::verbosity
helper) fails with 'undefined symbol: _ZN6LHAPDF6Config3getEv'.

Switching to 'lhapdf-config --libs' restores the link-time dependency
and fixes the runtime symbol lookup error.
---
 m4/acinclude.m4 | 2 +-
 1 file changed, 1 insertion(+), 1 deletion(-)

diff --git a/m4/acinclude.m4 b/m4/acinclude.m4
index f7cb003..f3a5189 100644
--- a/m4/acinclude.m4
+++ b/m4/acinclude.m4
@@ -756,7 +756,7 @@ AC_DEFUN([SHERPA_SETUP_CONFIGURE_OPTIONS],
       esac;
 
       if test -x "$CONDITIONAL_LHAPDFDIR/bin/lhapdf-config"; then
-        CONDITIONAL_LHAPDFLIBS="$($CONDITIONAL_LHAPDFDIR/bin/lhapdf-config --ldflags)";
+        CONDITIONAL_LHAPDFLIBS="$($CONDITIONAL_LHAPDFDIR/bin/lhapdf-config --libs)";
         CONDITIONAL_LHAPDFINCS="$($CONDITIONAL_LHAPDFDIR/bin/lhapdf-config --cppflags)";
         lhapdfversion="$($CONDITIONAL_LHAPDFDIR/bin/lhapdf-config --version)";
         lhapdfversion=${lhapdfversion:0:1}
